 tipos peque\u00f1os juntos para satisfacer reglas de alineaci\u00f3n eficientemente."}}]', NULL, '[{"id": "q4-1", "question": {"EN": "Does `Option<&i32>` use more memory than `&i32`?", "ES": "\u00bfUsa `Option<&i32>` m\u00e1s memoria que `&i32`?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Yes", "No"], "ES": ["S\u00ed", "No"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "No, thanks to Null Pointer Optimization, `None` is represented as the null address.", "ES": "No, gracias a la Optimizaci\u00f3n de Puntero Nulo, `None` se representa como direcci\u00f3n nula."}}, {"id": "q4-2", "question": {"EN": "Why does Rust reorder struct fields?", "ES": "\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 Rust reordena campos de structs?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Alphabetical sorting", "To reduce padding/size", "Randomly"], "ES": ["Orden alfab\u00e9tico", "Para reducir padding/tama\u00f1o", "Aleatoriamente"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "It packs smaller types together to satisfy alignment rules efficiently.", "ES": "Empaqueta tipos peque\u00f1os juntos para satisfacer reglas de alineaci\u00f3n eficientemente."}}]', NULL, 3);
INSERT INTO modules (id, course_id, title, "order") VALUES ('722ead79-0773-579b-b0c9-f9bef56d0105', '09e98e70-34ad-5a7c-90c9-47a3b1d55fcb', '{"EN": "5. Functions & Error Handling", "ES": "5. Funciones y Manejo de Errores"}', 5);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('a8afa97d-8454-5dfc-8320-233ee5cf6ad6', '722ead79-0773-579b-b0c9-f9bef56d0105', '{"EN": "Result Internals & The ? Operator", "ES": "Internos de Result y el Operador ?"}', '{"EN": "# The Result Enum\n```rust\nenum Result<T, E> {\n    Ok(T),\n    Err(E),\n}\n```\nIt works like any other enum. `#[must_use]` attribute forces you to handle it (compilation warning if ignored).\n\n## The `?` Operator (Propagate)\nSyntactic sugar for error propagation.\nIt performs 3 steps:\n1.  Matches the result.\n2.  If `Ok(v)`, extracts `v`.\n3.  If `Err(e)`, calls `From::from(e)` to convert the error into the function''s return error type, and returns early.\n\nThis automatic conversion allows you to mix different error types (like IO errors and Parse errors) into a unified application error type seamlessly.\n\n## Unwrapping\n*   `unwrap()`: If Err, calls `panic!` with a generic message.\n*   `expect(\"msg\")`: If Err, calls `panic!` with your message.\nPanicking unwinds the stack (calls destructors/drop) which is safe but expensive. Avoid in loops or libraries.", "ES": "# El Enum Result\nFunciona como cualquier otro enum. El atributo `#[must_use]` te fuerza a manejarlo (aviso de compilaci\u00f3n si se ignora).\n\n## El Operador `?` (Propagar)\nAz\u00facar sint\u00e1ctica para propagaci\u00f3n.\nRealiza 3 pasos:\n1.  Match del resultado.\n2.  Si `Ok(v)`, extrae `v`.\n3.  Si `Err(e)`, llama `From::from(e)` para convertir el error al tipo de error de retorno de la funci\u00f3n, y retorna temprano.\n\nEsta conversi\u00f3n autom\u00e1tica permite mezclar diferentes tipos de errores (como IO y Parseo) en un tipo de error unificado sin problemas.\n\n## Unwrapping\n*   `unwrap()`: Si Err, p\u00e1nico con mensaje gen\u00e9rico.\n*   `expect(\"msg\")`: Si Err, p\u00e1nico con tu mensaje.\nEl p\u00e1nico desenrolla el stack (llama destructores), lo cual es seguro pero costoso. Evitar en bucles o librer\u00edas."}', false, NULL, NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply(\"10\", \"2\") {\n        Ok(n) => println!(\"Result: {}\", n),\n        Err(e) => println!(\"Error parsing: {}\", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, E'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, E'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, E'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply(\"10\", \"2\") {\n        Ok(n) => println!(\"Result: {}\", n),\n        Err(e) => println!(\"Error parsing: {}\", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply(\"10\", \"2\") {\n        Ok(n) => println!(\"Result: {}\", n),\n        Err(e) => println!(\"Error parsing: {}\", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply("10", "2") {\n        Ok(n) => println!("Result: {}", n),\n        Err(e) => println!("Error parsing: {}", e),\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use std::num::ParseIntError;\n\n// Custom function combining logical steps\nfn multiply(first: &str, second: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    // ? propagates ParseIntError immediately if parsing fails\n    let n1 = first.parse::<i32>()?;\n    let n2 = second.parse::<i32>()?;\n    \n    Ok(n1 * n2)\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    match multiply(\"10\", \"2\") {\n        Ok(n) => println!(\"Result: {}\", n),\n        Err(e) => println!(\"Error parsing: {}\", e),\n    }\n}', 1);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('dd333124-e7bf-53e8-b327-b6d5da611cc0', '722ead79-0773-579b-b0c9-f9bef56d0105', '{"EN": "Closures & Functional Combinators", "ES": "Closures y Combinadores Funcionales"}', '{"EN": "# Functional Error Handling\nInstead of verbose `match` statements, Rust provides functional combinators on `Option` and `Result`.\n\n## Combinators\n*   `map`: Transform inner value `T`.\n*   `map_err`: Transform inner error `E`.\n*   `and_then`: (FlatMap) Input is `T`, output is `Result<U, E>`. Used for chaining operations that might fail.\n*   `unwrap_or_else`: Allows providing a closure to calculate a default value only if needed (lazy evaluation).\n\n## Closures in Depth\nClosures `|args| body` are syntactic sugar for structs that implement one of:\n*   `Fn`: Reads environment (Immutable borrow).\n*   `FnMut`: Modifies environment (Mutable borrow).\n*   `FnOnce`: Consumes environment (Move).", "ES": "# Manejo de Errores Funcional\nEn lugar de `match` verbosos, Rust provee combinadores funcionales.\n\n## Combinadores\n*   `map`: Transforma valor interno `T`.\n*   `map_err`: Transforma error interno `E`.\n*   `and_then`: (FlatMap) Entrada es `T`, salida es `Result<U, E>`. Usado para encadenar operaciones que pueden fallar.\n*   `unwrap_or_else`: Permite proveer un closure para calcular valor por defecto solo si es necesario (evaluaci\u00f3n perezosa).\n\n## Closures en Profundidad\nLos closures son az\u00facar sint\u00e1ctica para structs que implementan:\n*   `Fn`: Lee entorno (Pr\u00e9stamo inmutable).\n*   `FnMut`: Modifica entorno (Pr\u00e9stamo mutable).\n*   `FnOnce`: Consume entorno (Mueve)."}', false, NULL, NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = \"42\";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!(\"Number: {}\", n));\n        \n    println!(\"{:?}\", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!(\"Calculating expensive default...\");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, E'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, E'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, E'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = \"42\";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!(\"Number: {}\", n));\n        \n    println!(\"{:?}\", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!(\"Calculating expensive default...\");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = \"42\";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!(\"Number: {}\", n));\n        \n    println!(\"{:?}\", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!(\"Calculating expensive default...\");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = "42";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!("Number: {}", n));\n        \n    println!("{:?}", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!("Calculating expensive default...");\n        100\n    });\n}', NULL, 'fn main() {\n    let raw = \"42\";\n    \n    // Chain: Parse -> Multiply -> Stringify\n    let res = raw.parse::<i32>()\n        .map(|n| n * 2)\n        .map(|n| format!(\"Number: {}\", n));\n        \n    println!(\"{:?}\", res);\n    \n    // Lazy default\n    let missing: Option<i32> = None;\n    let val = missing.unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        println!(\"Calculating expensive default...\");\n        100\n    });\n}', 2);
