u00f3digo s\u00edncrono pesado en Tokio?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Just run it", "spawn_blocking", "async block"], "ES": ["Solo c\u00f3rrelo", "spawn_blocking", "bloque async"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "`spawn_blocking` moves it to a separate thread pool to avoid blocking the async event loop.", "ES": "`spawn_blocking` lo mueve a un pool separado para evitar bloquear el bucle de eventos."}}]', NULL, '[{"id": "q3-1", "question": {"EN": "What scheduling strategy does Tokio use?", "ES": "\u00bfQu\u00e9 estrategia de planificaci\u00f3n usa Tokio?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Round Robin", "Work Stealing", "FIFO"], "ES": ["Round Robin", "Robo de Trabajo (Work Stealing)", "FIFO"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Work Stealing allows idle threads to take tasks from busy threads.", "ES": "Work Stealing permite a hilos ociosos tomar tareas de hilos ocupados."}}, {"id": "q3-2", "question": {"EN": "How do you run synchronous CPU-heavy code in Tokio?", "ES": "\u00bfC\u00f3mo corres c\u00f3digo s\u00edncrono pesado en Tokio?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Just run it", "spawn_blocking", "async block"], "ES": ["Solo c\u00f3rrelo", "spawn_blocking", "bloque async"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "`spawn_blocking` moves it to a separate thread pool to avoid blocking the async event loop.", "ES": "`spawn_blocking` lo mueve a un pool separado para evitar bloquear el bucle de eventos."}}]', NULL, 5);
INSERT INTO modules (id, course_id, title, "order") VALUES ('cd1772a0-87b3-5262-8159-2302ce4a50f7', '2c20e72b-36b9-581d-a7de-b94661a4f498', '{"EN": "4. Async Patterns", "ES": "4. Patrones As\u00edncronos"}', 4);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('e385917a-2777-5251-ae19-034acc719ebe', 'cd1772a0-87b3-5262-8159-2302ce4a50f7', '{"EN": "Tokio Channels: MPSC Internals", "ES": "Canales Tokio: Internos de MPSC"}', '{"EN": "# Async Message Passing\nStandard channels (`std::sync::mpsc`) block the thread when waiting for a message. Tokio channels are async: `recv().await` registers a Waker and yields if the channel is empty.\n\n## MPSC (Multi-Producer, Single-Consumer)\nIdeal for the **Actor Pattern**: many components send commands to a single manager task processing them sequentially.\n\n### Backpressure (Bounded)\n`mpsc::channel(n)` creates a bounded channel.\nIf the channel is full (size `n`), calls to `send().await` will **block (yield)** the sender task. This creates natural **Backpressure**, propagating slowness from the consumer back to the producers, preventing memory explosions.\n\n### Unbounded\n`mpsc::unbounded_channel()`. `send()` is not async (it never waits). **Danger**: If producers are faster than the consumer, memory usage grows indefinitely (OOM). Only use if you know the rate is low.", "ES": "# Paso de Mensajes Async\nLos canales est\u00e1ndar bloquean el hilo. Los de Tokio son async: `recv().await` registra un Waker y cede si est\u00e1 vac\u00edo.\n\n## MPSC (Multi-Productor, Consumidor-\u00danico)\nIdeal para el **Patr\u00f3n Actor**: muchos componentes env\u00edan comandos a una tarea gestora \u00fanica.\n\n### Backpressure (Acotado)\n`mpsc::channel(n)` crea un canal acotado.\nSi est\u00e1 lleno, `send().await` **bloquea (cede)** al emisor. Esto crea **Backpressure** natural, propagando la lentitud del consumidor a los productores, preveniendo explosiones de memoria.\n\n### No Acotado\n`mpsc::unbounded_channel()`. `send()` no es async. **Peligro**: Si productores son m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidos, la memoria crece indefinidamente. \u00dasalo con cuidado."}', false, NULL, NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("Actor 2 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!("GOT = {}", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("Actor 2 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!("GOT = {}", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("Actor 2 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!("GOT = {}", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("Actor 2 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!("GOT = {}", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("Actor 2 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!("GOT = {}", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("Actor 2 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!("GOT = {}", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, 'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send(\"Actor 1 reporting\").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send(\"Actor 2 reporting\").await.unwrap();\n    });\n\n    while let Some(message) = rx.recv().await {\n        println!(\"GOT = {}\", message);\n    }\n}', NULL, E'use tokio::sync::mpsc;\n\n#[tokio::main]\nasync fn main() {\n    // Capacity 32. If 33 messages are sent before any read, the 33rd sender sleeps.\n    let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(32);\n\n    let tx2 = tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx.send("Actor 1 reporting").await.unwrap();\n    });\n    \n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        tx2.send("A