INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('e5e4fb8c-0975-55fd-a11c-adfb42c69a5c', 'ec52fcdb-46f8-5289-a434-f0d01828a624', '{"EN": "Derive Macros", "ES": "Macros Derive"}', '{"EN": "# The Derive Macro\n\nThis is the most common type (e.g., `#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]`). It creates new code *alongside* the struct or enum; it does not modify the original item.\n\n## How it works (The `syn` crate)\nWhen you put `#[derive(MyTrait)]` on a struct, your macro receives the *entire struct definition* as tokens.\n1.  Use `syn` to parse it into a `DeriveInput`.\n2.  Extract the struct name (`ident`).\n3.  Use `quote!` to generate an `impl MyTrait for StructName { ... }` block.\n\n## Quote Crate\nThe `quote!` macro lets you write Rust code inside your Rust code. It supports variable interpolation using `#variable`.", "ES": "# La Macro Derive\n\nEs el tipo m\u00e1s com\u00fan (ej. `#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]`). Crea nuevo c\u00f3digo *junto* al struct o enum; no modifica el \u00edtem original.\n\n## C\u00f3mo funciona (El crate `syn`)\nCuando pones `#[derive(MyTrait)]` en un struct, tu macro recibe la *definici\u00f3n entera del struct* como tokens.\n1.  Usa `syn` para parsearlo a un `DeriveInput`.\n2.  Extrae el nombre del struct (`ident`).\n3.  Usa `quote!` para generar un bloque `impl MyTrait for NombreStruct { ... }`.\n\n## Crate Quote\nLa macro `quote!` te permite escribir c\u00f3digo Rust dentro de tu c\u00f3digo Rust. Soporta interpolaci\u00f3n de variables usando `#variable`."}', false, NULL, NULL, '// Imaginary implementation of #[derive(Hello)]\n/*\nlet name = &ast.ident; // The struct name (e.g., "User")\n\n// quote! returns a TokenStream\nlet output = quote! {\n    impl Hello for #name {\n        fn hello() {\n            println!("Hello, I am {}!", stringify!(#name));\n        }\n    }\n};\n*/\n\nfn main() {\n    // User usage:\n    // #[derive(Hello)]\n    // struct User;\n    \n    // User::hello(); -> "Hello, I am 