ow()` without enabling the ''Window'' feature in Cargo.toml?", "ES": "\u00bfQu\u00e9 pasa si intentas usar `window()` sin habilitar la feature ''Window''?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Runtime Error", "Compiler Error (Function not found)", "It returns null"], "ES": ["Error de Runtime", "Error de Compilaci\u00f3n (Funci\u00f3n no encontrada)", "Retorna null"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "The function definition is literally compiled out via `#[cfg(feature = ...)]`.", "ES": "La definici\u00f3n de la funci\u00f3n es literalmente excluida de la compilaci\u00f3n v\u00eda `#[cfg(feature = ...)]`."}}]', NULL, 4);
INSERT INTO modules (id, course_id, title, "order") VALUES ('865d5bab-4474-5975-9c69-009c0e893cc6', '898cad9d-bd7e-56f1-9c18-543b46485883', '{"EN": "3. Yew & Frontend Architecture", "ES": "3. Yew y Arquitectura Frontend"}', 3);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('92025b33-4a5a-598f-9245-46868f76a47b', '865d5bab-4474-5975-9c69-009c0e893cc6', '{"EN": "Component Model & VDOM", "ES": "Modelo de Componentes y VDOM"}', '{"EN": "# Yew Architecture\nYew is a component-based framework similar to React, but strictly typed.\n*   **VDOM**: It maintains a Virtual DOM tree in WASM memory. When state changes, it diffs the tree and sends minimal patches to the real DOM via `web-sys`.\n*   **Component Trait**: The core abstraction.\n    *   `create`: Constructor.\n    *   `view`: Returns `Html`.\n    *   `update`: The message handler (Elm architecture).\n\n## Properties (Props)\nProps in Yew must implement `PartialEq`. Yew uses this to skip rendering if props haven''t changed.\nProps are usually wrapped in `Rc` (Reference Counted) implicitly to make cloning cheap, as they are passed down the tree.", "ES": "# Arquitectura Yew\nYew es similar a React pero tipado.\n*   **VDOM**: Mantiene un DOM Virtual en memoria WASM.\n*   **Trait Component**:\n    *   `create`: Constructor.\n    *   `view`: Retorna `Html`.\n    *   `update`: Manejador de mensajes (Arquitectura Elm).\n\n## Propiedades (Props)\nLas props deben implementar `PartialEq`. Yew usa esto para saltar renderizados si no han cambiado. Usualmente envueltas en `Rc` para clonaci\u00f3n barata."}', false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('b684539a-9a12-54d5-9539-d40742c8b502', '865d5bab-4474-5975-9c69-009c0e893cc6', '{"EN": "State Management & Context", "ES": "Gesti\u00f3n de Estado y Contexto"}', '{"EN": "# Message Passing\nIn the struct component model, components communicate via `Msg` enums.\n*   **Msg**: Defined in the component. Passed to `link.callback(...)`.\n*   **Update Loop**: When a callback fires, `update(msg)` is called. It returns a `bool` (should_render).\n\n## Function Components & Hooks\nModern Yew prefers Function Components using Hooks (`use_state`, `use_effect`).\nThis mimics React but handles Rust''s ownership rules differently (often requiring `clone()` of state handles before moving into closures).\n\n## Context API\nTo avoid \"Prop Drilling\", Yew provides `ContextProvider<T>`. Children consume context via `use_context::<T>()`.", "ES": "# Paso de Mensajes\nLos componentes se comunican v\u00eda enums `Msg`.\n*   **Bucle de Actualizaci\u00f3n**: Al dispararse un callback, se llama a `update(msg)`. Retorna `bool`.\n\n## Hooks\nYew moderno prefiere Componentes Funcionales con Hooks (`use_state`, `use_effect`). Imita a React pero requiere manejo cuidadoso de ownership (clonar handles antes de mover a closures).\n\n## Context API\nPara evitar \"Prop Drilling\", Yew provee `ContextProvider`."}', false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('59831c09-a391-5952-a0aa-f21085278870', '865d5bab-4474-5975-9c69-009c0e893cc6', '{"EN": "Agents & Workers", "ES": "Agentes y Workers"}', '{"EN": "# Offloading Work\nSince the UI thread must not block, heavy logic should run in Web Workers.\nYew (via `gloo-worker`) provides abstractions for Agents.\n*   **Agents**: Actors that run in a separate thread (Worker) or the same thread.\n*   **Bridges**: Mechanism to send messages to/from Agents.\n\nThis is critical for crypto apps where hashing/signing might take >10ms and freeze the UI.", "ES": "# Descargando Trabajo\nLa l\u00f3gica pesada debe correr en Web Workers.\nYew (v\u00eda `gloo-worker`) provee Agentes.\n*   **Agentes**: Actores que corren en otro hilo o el mismo.\n*   **Puentes**: Mecanismo para mensajes.\n\nCr\u00edtico para apps cripto donde hashear/firmar puede congelar la UI."}', false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('621aea48-20eb-567a-ab0d-ac2749fe385e', '865d5bab-4474-5975-9c69-009c0e893cc6', '{"EN": "Quiz: Frontend Architecture", "ES": "Quiz: Arquitectura Frontend"}', '{"EN": "Test Yew knowledge.", "ES": "Prueba conocimiento de Yew."}', true, NULL, '[{"id": "q-w3-3-1", "question": {"EN": "Why do Yew Props require `PartialEq`?", "ES": "\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 las Props de Yew requieren `PartialEq`?"}, "options": {"EN": ["To sort them", "To determine if the component needs re-rendering", "To print them"], "ES": ["Para ordenarlas", "Para determinar si el componente necesita re-renderizarse", "Para imprimirlas"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Yew compares new props with old props. If they are equal, it skips the expensive View + Patch cycle.", "ES": "Yew compara las nuevas props con las viejas. Si son iguales, salta el ciclo costoso de View + Patch."}}, {"id": "q-w3-3-2", "question": {"EN": "What is the primary difference between Yew Struct vs Function components?", "ES": "\u00bfDiferencia principal entre componentes Struct y Funci\u00f3n en Yew?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Structs are faster", "Structs use the Elm Message pattern, Functions use Hooks", "Functions cannot have state"], "ES": ["Structs son m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidos", "Structs usan patr\u00f3n Mensaje Elm, Funciones usan Hooks", "Funciones no tienen estado"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Struct components explicity implement the `Component` trait with an update loop. Functions manage state via hook closures.", "ES": "Los componentes Struct implementan expl\u00edcitamente el trait `Component`. Las funciones gestionan estado v\u00eda closures de hooks."}}]', NULL, '[{"id": "q-w3-3-1", "question": {"EN": "Why do Yew Props require `PartialEq`?", "ES": "\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 las Props de Yew requieren `PartialEq`?"}, "options": {"EN": ["To sort them", "To determine if the component needs re-rendering", "To print them"], "