al, it skips the expensive View + Patch cycle.", "ES": "Yew compara las nuevas props con las viejas. Si son iguales, salta el ciclo costoso de View + Patch."}}, {"id": "q-w3-3-2", "question": {"EN": "What is the primary difference between Yew Struct vs Function components?", "ES": "\u00bfDiferencia principal entre componentes Struct y Funci\u00f3n en Yew?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Structs are faster", "Structs use the Elm Message pattern, Functions use Hooks", "Functions cannot have state"], "ES": ["Structs son m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidos", "Structs usan patr\u00f3n Mensaje Elm, Funciones usan Hooks", "Funciones no tienen estado"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Struct components explicity implement the `Component` trait with an update loop. Functions manage state via hook closures.", "ES": "Los componentes Struct implementan expl\u00edcitamente el trait `Component`. Las funciones gestionan estado v\u00eda closures de hooks."}}]', NULL, '[{"id": "q-w3-3-1", "question": {"EN": "Why do Yew Props require `PartialEq`?", "ES": "\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 las Props de Yew requieren `PartialEq`?"}, "options": {"EN": ["To sort them", "To determine if the component needs re-rendering", "To print them"], "ES": ["Para ordenarlas", "Para determinar si el componente necesita re-renderizarse", "Para imprimirlas"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Yew compares new props with old props. If they are equal, it skips the expensive View + Patch cycle.", "ES": "Yew compara las nuevas props con las viejas. Si son iguales, salta el ciclo costoso de View + Patch."}}, {"id": "q-w3-3-2", "question": {"EN": "What is the primary difference between Yew Struct vs Function components?", "ES": "\u00bfDiferencia principal entre componentes Struct y Funci\u00f3n en Yew?"}, "options": {"EN": ["Structs are faster", "Structs use the Elm Message pattern, Functions use Hooks", "Functions cannot have state"], "ES": ["Structs son m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidos", "Structs usan patr\u00f3n Mensaje Elm, Funciones usan Hooks", "Funciones no tienen estado"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Struct components explicity implement the `Component` trait with an update loop. Functions manage state via hook closures.", "ES": "Los componentes Struct implementan expl\u00edcitamente el trait `Component`. Las funciones gestionan estado v\u00eda closures de hooks."}}]', NULL, 4);
INSERT INTO modules (id, course_id, title, "order") VALUES ('e3c22e32-aed7-5455-96ef-938b1a48dc99', '898cad9d-bd7e-56f1-9c18-543b46485883', '{"EN": "4. Advanced Cryptography in WASM", "ES": "4. Criptograf\u00eda Avanzada en WASM"}', 4);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('50e4c5c3-7f47-5472-9754-d3381d016cc8', 'e3c22e32-aed7-5455-96ef-938b1a48dc99', '{"EN": "Entropy & Randomness Source", "ES": "Entrop\u00eda y Fuentes de Aleatoriedad"}', '{"EN": "# The Entropy Problem\nStandard `rand::thread_rng()` relies on OS syscalls (`/dev/urandom`). In WASM, these do not exist.\nThe `getrandom` crate must be configured with the `js` feature.\n*   **Mechanism**: It calls `window.crypto.getRandomValues()` (Browser) or `crypto.randomBytes()` (Node.js).\n*   **Failure**: If not configured or context is missing, it panics.\n\n## Security Warning\nNever implement your own PRNG (Pseudo-Random Number Generator) for keys. Always use the CSPRNG provided by the environment via `getrandom`.", "ES": "# El Problema de la Entrop\u00eda\n`rand::thread_rng()` depende de syscalls. En WASM no existen.\nEl crate `getrandom` debe configurarse con la feature `js`.\n*   **Mecanismo**: Llama a `window.crypto`.\n*   **Fallo**: Si no se configura, p\u00e1nico.\n\n## Advertencia de Seguridad\nNunca implementes tu propio PRNG para claves. Usa siempre el CSPRNG del entorno."}', false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('382bef78-b5fd-5fc9-a4c5-2828c649104a', 'e3c22e32-aed7-5455-96ef-938b1a48dc99', '{"EN": "Constant-Time Execution", "ES": "Ejecuci\u00f3n de Tiempo Constante"}', '{"EN": "# Timing Attacks\nCryptography code must run in \"Constant Time\" regardless of the input (keys) to prevent side-channel attacks.\n*   **WASM Challenge**: The WASM spec does not guarantee constant-time instructions. The browser JIT (Just-In-Time) compiler might optimize code branches differently based on data.\n*   **Mitigation**: Use pure Rust crypto crates (`k256`, `ed25519-dalek`) that use subtle arithmetic tricks to avoid conditional branches on secret data. Avoid calling JS-native crypto for primitives if you need guaranteed behavior consistency.", "ES": "# Ataques de Tiempo\nEl c\u00f3digo criptogr\u00e1fico debe correr en \"Tiempo Constante\".\n*   **Reto WASM**: La especificaci\u00f3n no garantiza instrucciones de tiempo constante. El JIT del navegador puede optimizar ramas.\n*   **Mitigaci\u00f3n**: Usa crates puros de Rust (`k256`) que usen trucos aritm\u00e9ticos para evitar ramas condicionales en datos secretos."}', false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('017ad84d-fc97-50e2-8bd5-e0c37464cc24', 'e3c22e32-aed7-5455-96ef-938b1a48dc99', '{"EN": "BigInt & Performance (u64 vs u32)", "ES": "BigInt y Rendimiento (u64 vs u32)"}', '{"EN": "# 64-bit Arithmetic\nElliptic Curve Cryptography heavily relies on 64-bit and 256-bit math.\n*   **wasm32**: Native support for `i64`, but sending `i64` to JS requires BigInt support (modern browsers only).\n*   **Performance**: Rust emulates `u128` math in software. While slower than native, WASM is still usually 10x-20x faster than pure JS implementations of the same math.\n\n## Zero-Copy hashing\nWhen hashing a file:\n1.  Allocate buffer in WASM.\n2.  Stream bytes directly into that view.\n3.  Run `Sha256::update`.\nDo NOT read the file into a JS string and pass it to Rust (double allocation).", "ES": "# Aritm\u00e9tica de 64 bits\nLa criptograf\u00eda de Curva El\u00edptica depende de matem\u00e1tica de 64 y 256 bits.\n*   **wasm32**: Soporte nativo para `i64`.\n*   **Rendimiento**: Rust emula matem\u00e1tica `u128` en software. A\u00fan as\u00ed, suele ser 10-20x m\u00e1s r\u00e1pido que JS puro.\n\n## Hashing Zero-Copy\nAl hashear un archivo: Transmite bytes directamente a la vista de memoria WASM. NO leas el archivo a un string JS."}', false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3);
INSERT INTO chapters (id, module_id, title, content, is_quiz, quiz_data, "order") VALUES ('0638df27-1442-56f7-b1a4-66a9e0814bbb', 'e3c22e32-aed7-5455-96ef-938b1a48dc99', '{"EN": "Quiz: Crypto Security", "ES": "Quiz: Seguridad Cripto"}', '{"EN": "Verify secure coding practices.", "ES": "Verificar pr\u00e1cticas seguras."}', true, NULL, '[{"id": "q-w3-4-1", "question": {"EN": "Why is JIT compilation a risk for cryptography?", "ES": "\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 la compilaci\u00f3n JIT es un riesgo para la criptograf\u00eda?"}, "options": {"EN": ["It makes code too slow", "It might introduce non-constant-time optimizations based on input data", "It consumes too much memory"], "ES": ["Hace el c\u00f3digo muy lento", "Puede introducir optimizaciones de tiempo no constante basadas en datos", "Consume mucha memoria"]}, "correctIndex": 1, "explanation": {"EN": "Timing attacks rely on measuring execution time to guess keys. JIT optimizations can inadvertently reveal secrets by making specific branches faster.", "ES": "Los ataques de tiempo miden la ejecuci\u00f3n para adivinar claves. Las optimizaciones JIT pueden revelar secretos haciendo ramas espec\u00edficas m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidas."}}, {"id": "q-w3-4-2", "question": {"EN": "How does `getrandom` work in a browser environment?", "ES": "\u00bfC\u00f3mo funciona `getrandom` en un entorno de navegador?"}, "options": {"EN": ["It reads /dev/random", "It uses the CPU clock", "It invokes `window.crypto.getRandomValues`"], "ES": ["Lee /dev/random", "Usa el reloj CPU", "Invoca `window.crypto.getRandomValues`"]}, "correctIndex": 2, "explanation": {"EN": "Since WASM has no OS access, it bridges to the browser''s CSPRNG API.", "ES": "Como WASM no tiene acceso al SO, hace puente a la API CSPRNG del navegador."}}]', NULL, '[{"id": "q-w3-4-1", "question": {"EN": "Why is JIT compilation a risk for cryptography?", "ES": "\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 la compilaci\u00f3n JIT es un riesgo para la criptograf\u00eda?"}, "options": {"EN": ["It makes code too slow", 